The Durban based Hawks’ South African Narcotics Enforcement Bureau recovered canvas bags with 265 bricks of cocaine estimated at R111 million at the Durban Harbour on Saturday. Hawks spokesperson, Warrant Officer Bonnie Nxumalo, said they are investigating the source or the link regarding the recovery of the consignment of suspected cocaine that was found in a vessel. “On Saturday, the Hawks team and SAPS Operational Response Services were alerted about a suspicious consignment in a vessel that was ferrying trucks. The team arrived at the said place and recovered canvas bags with 265 bricks of cocaine. The drugs have an estimated value of R111 million. Preliminary investigations were conducted and the ownership of the shipment could not be located,” said Nxumalo. The drugs were seized subject to an ongoing investigation. No arrests have yet been made at this stage.